Introduction and Overview

This report provides a detailed analysis of Walmart Inc. (WMT), a 840.50 B company, operating in the Discount Stores industry. The core questions for investors is whether the current stock price represents a fair value and if the company is well-positioned for future growth. Would it be wise to invest in Walmart Inc. at this moment? Let's see how well WMT stock performs in the current market.

Here's What You Need to Know Right Now

The stock is currently trading at $105.32 (as of November 2025), and it's showing positive momentum, trading above both its 50-day and 200-day moving averages.

Analysts appear optimistic, with a 1-year price target of $118.21 (a potential +27.0% upside). However, there's significant volatility here (22.8% annualized), suggesting the potential for wide price swings.

Walmart Inc.'s fundamental story is nuanced. On one hand, the company benefits from a portfolio of established brands. On the other, it faces challenges with intense competition in its sector.

Company Description

A brief overview of the company's business activities. Walmart Inc. engages in the operation of retail and wholesale stores and clubs, eCommerce websites, and mobile applications worldwide.

The company operates through three segments: Walmart U.S., Walmart International, and Sam's Club. It operates supercenters, supermarkets, warehouse clubs, cash and carry stores, and discount stores under Walmart and Walmart Neighborhood Market brands; membership-only warehouse clubs;

and ecommerce websites, such as walmart.com.mx, walmart.ca, flipkart.com, PhonePe and other sites.

The company also offers grocery items, including dry grocery, snacks, dairy, meat, produce, deli and bakery, frozen foods, alcoholic and nonalcoholic beverages, as well as consumables, such as health and beauty aids, pet supplies, household chemicals, paper goods, and baby products;

and fuel and other categories. In addition, it is involved in the provision of health and wellness products covering pharmacy, optical and hearing services, over-the-counter drugs, and protein and nutrition products;

and home, hardlines, and seasonal items, including home improvement, outdoor living, gardening, furniture, apparel, jewelry, tools and power equipment, housewares, toys, and mattresses. Further, the company offers consumer electronics and accessories, software, video games, office supplies, appliances, and third-party gift cards. Additionally, it operates digital payment platforms;

offers financial services and related products, including money transfers, bill payments, money orders, check cashing, prepaid access, co-branded credit cards, installment lending, and earned wage access; and markets lines of merchandise under private and licensed brands.

The company was formerly known as Wal-Mart Stores, Inc. and changed its name to Walmart Inc. in February 2018. Walmart Inc. was founded in 1945 and is based in Bentonville, Arkansas.

Total Valuation

Although the market considers Walmart Inc. to be a key player in the Discount Stores industry with a 840.50 B market cap, its enterprise value is much higher at 897.63 B, with 57.13B of that value added by debt. The valuation ratios tell an interesting story: at 1.30x revenue and 21.07x EBITDA, Walmart Inc. trades at a premium to many peers. This reflects the company's strong market position and brand assets. But it also means the stock may have little room for error. The upcoming 2026-02-19 earnings report will be crucial in showing whether Walmart Inc.'s businesses can grow into this valuation, while the 2025-12-12 ex-dividend date serves as a reminder that Walmart Inc. still rewards shareholders even as it invests for growth. Essentially, you're paying for quality - but quality doesn't come cheap.

Financial Health

WMTs financial data clearly shows that strengths and weaknesses can appear together. The Current Ratio of 0.79x and Quick Ratio of 0.19x show potential liquidity issues that might cause trouble if the company's cash cycle lengthens. Furthermore, WMT's 8.34 B in levered free cash flow suggests it can still generate significant cash for shareholders even after meeting its financial obligations.

Financial Efficiency

Walmart's Asset Turnover (2.66x) suggests it generates $2.66 in revenue per dollar of assets, indicating excellent efficiency in utilizing its asset base. Inventory Turnover (9.07x) shows Walmart reasonably sells and replaces inventory roughly 9.1 times annually, translating to 40.2 Days Inventory Outstanding. The Working Capital Turnover (-40.47x) indicates concerning use of short-term assets to support sales, supported by a Current Ratio (0.79x), signaling potential liquidity concerns.

The Cash Conversion Cycle (~45.5 days (partial)) suggests it takes about 1.5 months to convert inventory and receivables into cash, indicating good cash flow efficiency. Walmart's Return on Invested Capital (16.41%) indicates strong capital efficiency, showing how effectively Walmart generates returns from its invested capital. Overall, Walmart demonstrates effective asset management that supports strong profitability. Investors should compare these figures with industry peers to assess competitive positioning.

Profitability and Growth

An analysis of the key metrics in WMT's margin performance shows the company has solid control over its costs and prices. The company is successful in controlling its production costs, as shown by the gross margin of 24.91%, and it also profits well from its core operations, reflected in the 4.39% operating margin. A 6.19% EBITDA margin indicates WMT is capable of generating strong cash flow from its operations before accounting for financing and tax strategies. All things considered, WMT can hold onto around $3.080 in net profit for every $1 of its revenue over the last twelve months. While the business's revenue is increasing at an aggressive rate (4.80%), investors should monitor if this pace can be sustained without eroding profit margins.

WMT's 42.88 B in EBITDA and 172.67 B in gross profit indicate its raw earning power, while the 21.34 B in net income reveals how effectively it converts that power into bottom-line results. The company appears to be balancing its pursuit of growth with the need to maintain profitability. Despite healthy gross margins, there is a significant difference between the company's gross and net margins (24.91% vs. 3.08%). This is likely due to high operating expenses, interest costs, or taxes, which are key areas for investors to watch. In the future, maintaining steady or improving margins will be critical. WMT needs to defend its pricing power and control operating costs, as this will help sustain profitability, especially if revenue growth moderates.

Dividends and Shareholder Returns

Dividend Summary & Investor Implications

The company currently offers a $0.94 annual dividend per share, translating to a dividend yield of 0.89%‚Äîmeaning for every $100 invested, shareholders receive $0.94 in dividends annually. This yield is below the 5-year average of 1.35%, suggesting that either the stock price has risen (reducing the yield) or dividend growth hasn't kept pace with historical trends.

Key Observations & Analysis:

  • The payout ratio of 31.91% is healthy, indicating the company uses only ~32% of its earnings to fund dividends. This leaves ample room for future increases or reinvestment in growth.
  • The very low trailing yield of 1.00% hints at a recent dividend initiation or a special, non-recurring payout, warranting further checks for consistency.
  • Investors must own the stock before the upcoming ex-dividend date of 2025-12-12 to receive the next dividend.

Investor Takeaway:

  • Income Investors: The modest yield and low payout ratio suggest dividends are safe but not a primary reason to invest. The focus may be on future dividend growth.
  • Growth Investors: The low payout ratio is a strong signal that a majority of earnings are being reinvested, which could drive future price appreciation.
  • Watch For: Announcements of dividend hikes (which could bring the yield closer to its historical average) or significant stock price changes that would alter the yield.
